1
00:01:30,800 --> 00:01:34,520
=Lady Liberty=

2
00:01:35,020 --> 00:01:37,940
=Episode 23=

3
00:01:40,780 --> 00:01:41,940
(Subject: Chapter 56: Cold Shadows
in a Swallow Cage Attachment added)

4
00:01:41,940 --> 00:01:43,460
(Chapter 56: Cold Shadows
in a Swallow Cage)

5
00:01:44,100 --> 00:01:46,700
(Send)

6
00:01:57,520 --> 00:01:58,160
Done?

7
00:01:58,200 --> 00:01:58,640
Yeah.

8
00:02:01,200 --> 00:02:02,080
You can renew now.

9
00:02:05,880 --> 00:02:06,880
Table 45, renew.

10
00:02:09,160 --> 00:02:09,560
Bye.

11
00:02:10,800 --> 00:02:11,480
How long?

12
00:02:12,120 --> 00:02:12,960
Two more hours.

13
00:02:13,100 --> 00:02:16,740
(E-Sports Internet Cafe Arcade)

14
00:02:19,740 --> 00:02:21,940
(Mengtong Internet Cafe)

15
00:02:30,222 --> 00:02:32,111
I brought you some late-night supper.

16
00:02:36,844 --> 00:02:37,733
I'm not hungry.

17
00:02:38,400 --> 00:02:39,400
Give it to San Mei.

18
00:02:40,777 --> 00:02:42,888
Was there something wrong
with my manuscript?

19
00:02:43,280 --> 00:02:43,640
No.

20
00:02:43,800 --> 00:02:44,733
It was really good.

21
00:02:45,440 --> 00:02:46,000
I'm worried

22
00:02:46,000 --> 00:02:47,640
it's too similar to my old style.

23
00:02:47,640 --> 00:02:48,888
People might recognize it,

24
00:02:49,040 --> 00:02:50,040
especially Lin Zhanqiao.

25
00:02:50,040 --> 00:02:51,360
She's very sensitive about that.

26
00:02:51,720 --> 00:02:52,440
I'm not worried.

27
00:03:03,400 --> 00:03:05,466
You actually hope
she figures it out, don't you?

28
00:03:06,560 --> 00:03:07,640
I'm just curious

29
00:03:07,800 --> 00:03:08,960
what expression she would have

30
00:03:08,960 --> 00:03:09,960
if she knew the truth.

31
00:03:09,960 --> 00:03:10,960
You're not curious.

32
00:03:12,040 --> 00:03:12,920
You want to win.

33
00:03:13,680 --> 00:03:14,280
Is that wrong?

34
00:03:14,533 --> 00:03:15,844
Who doesn't want to win?

35
00:03:17,520 --> 00:03:19,400
Aren't you busy preparing
for your wedding?

36
00:03:19,511 --> 00:03:21,311
You don't have to come see me
all the time.

37
00:03:21,320 --> 00:03:23,844
Didn't you say Lin Zhanqiao
doesn't spend enough time with you?

38
00:03:23,920 --> 00:03:25,040
But you're not her.

39
00:03:27,080 --> 00:03:28,120
Just think of it as

40
00:03:28,360 --> 00:03:29,640
me wanting to see you.

41
00:03:30,600 --> 00:03:32,640
You're a trophy I earned myself.

42
00:03:32,920 --> 00:03:34,040
Seeing you every day

43
00:03:34,040 --> 00:03:35,280
is my reward.

44
00:03:35,600 --> 00:03:37,160
This is my need, not yours.

45
00:03:37,333 --> 00:03:38,280
What about Ling Yikai?

46
00:03:38,920 --> 00:03:39,880
Is he your trophy, too?

47
00:03:40,960 --> 00:03:41,360
Yeah.

48
00:03:42,120 --> 00:03:42,720
A big one.

49
00:03:43,288 --> 00:03:44,400
Yours isn't small either.

50
00:03:46,840 --> 00:03:48,520
Why do you need so many trophies?

51
00:03:48,720 --> 00:03:49,800
To prove I'm good.

52
00:03:54,422 --> 00:03:55,311
Where are you going?

53
00:03:55,840 --> 00:03:56,680
Er Jiu's shoes broke.

54
00:03:56,680 --> 00:03:57,977
I'm going to buy him a new pair.

55
00:04:06,080 --> 00:04:07,120
If I didn't work this hard,

56
00:04:07,400 --> 00:04:08,520
I would end up like her.

57
00:04:11,920 --> 00:04:13,120
She's happier than you.

58
00:04:14,000 --> 00:04:14,880
You think that

59
00:04:14,880 --> 00:04:16,560
because she sees you happy.

60
00:04:17,440 --> 00:04:19,160
If you hadn't become Gu Yan,

61
00:04:19,480 --> 00:04:20,600
the one marrying her now

62
00:04:20,880 --> 00:04:21,680
would be you.

63
00:04:24,600 --> 00:04:25,400
If I were her,

64
00:04:26,000 --> 00:04:27,320
I would never let you go.

65
00:04:28,880 --> 00:04:29,840
She's not like you.

66
00:04:30,666 --> 00:04:31,688
You never know.

67
00:04:36,360 --> 00:04:37,160
Starting tomorrow,

68
00:04:37,360 --> 00:04:39,080
you'll be the only top author on Dingqi.

69
00:04:39,680 --> 00:04:40,680
Drunk Old Friend

70
00:04:40,690 --> 00:04:42,866
and Parting with Yan Dan at Yishui
Sequel are both yours.

71
00:04:42,920 --> 00:04:44,444
Once Shattered Six States is finished,

72
00:04:44,680 --> 00:04:46,520
He Han's name won't appear
on the rankings

73
00:04:46,520 --> 00:04:47,400
for a long time.

74
00:04:48,960 --> 00:04:50,360
I heard he's starting a new novel.

75
00:04:51,466 --> 00:04:53,000
I don't think he's in his element.

76
00:05:05,080 --> 00:05:05,440
Hello?

77
00:05:05,880 --> 00:05:07,640
Was it you or Zhang Yousen
who reported me?

78
00:05:08,280 --> 00:05:08,840
Reported?

79
00:05:10,080 --> 00:05:10,800
Reported what?

80
00:05:11,111 --> 00:05:13,622
Representing both plaintiff
and defendant at the same time.

81
00:05:14,600 --> 00:05:15,800
Our firm is large

82
00:05:16,160 --> 00:05:17,040
and capable.

83
00:05:17,840 --> 00:05:19,240
It's normal for both sides

84
00:05:19,640 --> 00:05:21,000
to come to us.

85
00:05:22,720 --> 00:05:24,360
We choose one side to represent,

86
00:05:24,520 --> 00:05:26,880
and refer the other to suitable lawyers.

87
00:05:27,200 --> 00:05:28,320
What's the problem with that?

88
00:05:28,720 --> 00:05:30,040
It's completely standard practice.

89
00:05:30,800 --> 00:05:31,880
So many former associates

90
00:05:31,880 --> 00:05:33,160
have come through my firm.

91
00:05:33,480 --> 00:05:35,600
Of course,
there are connections everywhere.

92
00:05:35,977 --> 00:05:37,933
If you insist on saying we're connected,

93
00:05:38,200 --> 00:05:40,160
you can spin it however you like.

94
00:05:43,680 --> 00:05:43,960
Hello?

95
00:05:51,200 --> 00:05:52,440
Sir, make a U-turn ahead.

96
00:05:52,440 --> 00:05:53,755
I'm changing my destination.

97
00:06:05,400 --> 00:06:05,920
Zhang Yousen.

98
00:06:08,440 --> 00:06:09,760
Why did you report Lawyer Bei?

99
00:06:13,200 --> 00:06:14,240
In the case between

100
00:06:14,240 --> 00:06:16,360
Xianding Company and Qiyou Company,

101
00:06:16,466 --> 00:06:18,000
he represented the plaintiff himself,

102
00:06:18,000 --> 00:06:19,560
and behind the scenes,
through your company,

103
00:06:19,560 --> 00:06:22,244
he referred the defendant to his
own student and former colleague.

104
00:06:22,360 --> 00:06:23,720
If this gets exposed, damage to his

105
00:06:23,840 --> 00:06:25,400
reputation in the industry
is the least of it.

106
00:06:25,400 --> 00:06:28,133
If it's investigated further,
he could receive a formal warning.

107
00:06:28,240 --> 00:06:29,440
He's also suspected of bribery.

108
00:06:29,670 --> 00:06:31,990
Getting his license revoked
would be the lightest punishment.

109
00:06:32,000 --> 00:06:33,622
In serious cases, he could be arrested.

110
00:06:33,720 --> 00:06:35,688
But that's not a reason for you
to report him.

111
00:06:36,111 --> 00:06:37,911
I warned Mrs. Bei
not to lay a finger on you.

112
00:06:37,933 --> 00:06:39,080
She refused to listen.

113
00:06:39,090 --> 00:06:40,777
I don't rely on reputation
or connections

114
00:06:40,822 --> 00:06:42,120
to keep my job or earn my salary.

115
00:06:42,760 --> 00:06:44,000
Whatever tricks Mrs. Bei pulled

116
00:06:44,000 --> 00:06:45,400
don't really affect me.

117
00:06:45,822 --> 00:06:47,111
But what you did to Lawyer Bei

118
00:06:47,120 --> 00:06:47,990
is a different matter.

119
00:06:48,000 --> 00:06:48,755
Fine.

120
00:06:49,480 --> 00:06:51,560
Then let's see
how the all-powerful Lawyer Bei

121
00:06:51,800 --> 00:06:53,720
handles a case that lands on himself.

122
00:06:53,911 --> 00:06:55,422
Mrs. Bei wanted to see you today

123
00:06:55,488 --> 00:06:56,311
to talk about this.

124
00:06:56,400 --> 00:06:58,333
I told her
it has nothing to do with you.

125
00:06:59,377 --> 00:07:01,066
She brought this on Lawyer Bei herself.

126
00:07:03,488 --> 00:07:04,760
Get in. I'll give you a ride.

127
00:07:10,533 --> 00:07:12,040
You have a perfectly good job.

128
00:07:12,040 --> 00:07:13,333
What exactly are you trying to do?

129
00:07:13,360 --> 00:07:14,560
I'm not acting recklessly.

130
00:07:17,600 --> 00:07:19,450
I think things through
before I make a move.

131
00:07:19,466 --> 00:07:20,822
That's what Lawyer Bei taught me.

132
00:07:22,288 --> 00:07:23,311
Zhou Mei, listen.

133
00:07:24,120 --> 00:07:24,560
First,

134
00:07:25,480 --> 00:07:26,880
I can protect you

135
00:07:27,200 --> 00:07:28,200
with my own strength

136
00:07:28,200 --> 00:07:29,200
and without hesitation.

137
00:07:30,520 --> 00:07:31,520
I'm not like Lawyer Bei.

138
00:07:31,520 --> 00:07:33,622
I can give you a hundred percent
of what I have.

139
00:07:34,000 --> 00:07:35,720
He can only give you a fifth of his.

140
00:07:35,720 --> 00:07:36,800
Maybe even just a tenth.

141
00:07:37,080 --> 00:07:38,760
Yes, my hundred percent

142
00:07:38,760 --> 00:07:39,880
may not match his fifth

143
00:07:39,880 --> 00:07:40,620
or tenth for now.

144
00:07:40,680 --> 00:07:41,720
But it'll keep growing.

145
00:07:41,720 --> 00:07:43,080
One day, it will surpass him.

146
00:07:47,320 --> 00:07:47,800
Second,

147
00:07:51,160 --> 00:07:51,840
I'm not perfect.

148
00:07:53,480 --> 00:07:54,440
But neither is he.

149
00:08:05,800 --> 00:08:07,160
The overall layout

150
00:08:07,160 --> 00:08:07,960
is pretty solid.

151
00:08:07,960 --> 00:08:09,110
No need to redo
the core structure.

152
00:08:09,120 --> 00:08:10,480
Even the paintings and books,

153
00:08:10,480 --> 00:08:12,000
you can keep them later if you want.

154
00:08:13,840 --> 00:08:14,840
Miss Lin, you're back.

155
00:08:15,120 --> 00:08:16,440
I'm showing the place to a client.

156
00:08:16,511 --> 00:08:17,590
Sorry for the disturbance.

157
00:08:17,800 --> 00:08:18,480
Go ahead.

158
00:08:18,560 --> 00:08:18,880
Okay.

159
00:08:21,160 --> 00:08:22,080
I have an idea.

160
00:08:22,880 --> 00:08:23,680
There are

161
00:08:23,680 --> 00:08:25,120
three fan groups, right?

162
00:08:25,520 --> 00:08:27,400
Everyone writes a letter

163
00:08:27,400 --> 00:08:28,640
to Mr. He Han,

164
00:08:28,920 --> 00:08:31,240
and adds our digital signature,

165
00:08:31,240 --> 00:08:31,990
honestly expressing

166
00:08:32,066 --> 00:08:34,288
why we don't want Shattered Six States
to be discontinued

167
00:08:34,640 --> 00:08:35,840
or rushed to an ending.

168
00:08:36,160 --> 00:08:37,680
Maybe that'll move him.

169
00:08:38,520 --> 00:08:39,360
You're wrong.

170
00:08:39,360 --> 00:08:40,600
Mr. He Han is definitely not

171
00:08:40,800 --> 00:08:42,080
as cold and emotionless

172
00:08:42,280 --> 00:08:44,440
as you think.

173
00:08:46,977 --> 00:08:48,333
What are you doing?

174
00:08:51,040 --> 00:08:51,800
Uh...

175
00:08:52,000 --> 00:08:53,440
Someone's here to view the place.

176
00:08:53,440 --> 00:08:54,920
The agent brought them.

177
00:08:55,044 --> 00:08:56,080
They're in the living room.

178
00:08:56,320 --> 00:08:57,360
I'm not scolding you.

179
00:08:57,920 --> 00:08:58,880
Why are you so nervous?

180
00:09:01,680 --> 00:09:03,080
I was afraid you would hear

181
00:09:03,288 --> 00:09:04,400
that I'm working on things

182
00:09:04,400 --> 00:09:06,080
for Mr. He Han's fan group again

183
00:09:06,640 --> 00:09:07,440
and get upset.

184
00:09:09,560 --> 00:09:10,560
You're already off work.

185
00:09:10,666 --> 00:09:13,022
You've finished everything
you needed to do.

186
00:09:13,960 --> 00:09:15,400
Using your free time

187
00:09:15,880 --> 00:09:17,200
to pursue your own interests.

188
00:09:17,888 --> 00:09:19,688
I have no right to criticize that.

189
00:09:24,240 --> 00:09:24,840
Ms. Lin,

190
00:09:25,160 --> 00:09:26,400
do you know anything?

191
00:09:27,680 --> 00:09:29,320
Why did Mr. He Han

192
00:09:29,320 --> 00:09:31,200
suddenly decide to end

193
00:09:31,200 --> 00:09:32,133
Shattered Six States?

194
00:09:38,640 --> 00:09:39,320
I don't know.

195
00:09:40,040 --> 00:09:40,600
If we try to

196
00:09:41,200 --> 00:09:42,840
stop him,

197
00:09:42,933 --> 00:09:44,133
do you think it's possible?

198
00:09:46,888 --> 00:09:48,333
Whether it's possible or not,

199
00:09:50,000 --> 00:09:50,800
any author

200
00:09:51,560 --> 00:09:52,720
would be moved

201
00:09:52,800 --> 00:09:54,120
to see their readers

202
00:09:54,577 --> 00:09:55,800
love their story this much.

203
00:09:58,160 --> 00:09:59,600
Sorry, I'll take this place.

204
00:10:00,400 --> 00:10:01,640
- Sorry.
- What's going on, Li?

205
00:10:01,640 --> 00:10:02,800
- Sorry.
- I think I hear my dad's voice.

206
00:10:02,800 --> 00:10:03,720
- You told us to come.
- I'm so sorry.

207
00:10:05,311 --> 00:10:06,920
- He's buying this place.
- You're wasting our time.

208
00:10:06,920 --> 00:10:08,040
- Jeez.
- I'm so sorry.

209
00:10:08,040 --> 00:10:09,560
- What is this all about?
- Let's go.

210
00:10:10,360 --> 00:10:10,880
I'm so sorry.

211
00:10:11,400 --> 00:10:12,840
I'm late.

212
00:10:12,880 --> 00:10:14,244
The company executives

213
00:10:14,311 --> 00:10:15,840
suddenly came for an inspection,

214
00:10:16,520 --> 00:10:18,160
so I got delayed.

215
00:10:18,520 --> 00:10:18,920
Did I

216
00:10:19,560 --> 00:10:20,680
mess anything up?

217
00:10:22,360 --> 00:10:23,480
Well, you can head back.

218
00:10:23,600 --> 00:10:24,622
I'm taking this place.

219
00:10:24,888 --> 00:10:25,840
Miss Lin, what is this?

220
00:10:26,960 --> 00:10:27,680
I'm really sorry.

221
00:10:27,840 --> 00:10:28,760
I'm not quite sure

222
00:10:28,760 --> 00:10:29,760
what's going on either.

223
00:10:30,360 --> 00:10:31,440
I'll call you later.

224
00:10:31,440 --> 00:10:32,644
You should go. You look busy.

225
00:10:32,920 --> 00:10:33,680
Thank you.

226
00:10:34,666 --> 00:10:35,480
What's going on?

227
00:10:35,480 --> 00:10:35,840
See you.

228
00:10:37,320 --> 00:10:38,360
What are you doing?

229
00:10:39,244 --> 00:10:40,933
You're selling the house, aren't you?

230
00:10:41,266 --> 00:10:42,200
You sell the house,

231
00:10:42,400 --> 00:10:43,200
and I buy the house.

232
00:10:44,560 --> 00:10:45,880
How can that work?

233
00:10:46,680 --> 00:10:47,360
Why not?

234
00:10:48,080 --> 00:10:49,200
Are you picking your buyers?

235
00:10:51,440 --> 00:10:52,240
Who gets to buy

236
00:10:52,240 --> 00:10:53,400
and who doesn't?

237
00:10:54,120 --> 00:10:55,120
You put it on sale.

238
00:10:55,640 --> 00:10:56,840
I think the price is fair.

239
00:10:56,960 --> 00:10:57,711
I'll take it.

240
00:10:58,822 --> 00:11:00,088
You need to sell urgently.

241
00:11:00,155 --> 00:11:01,444
I need to buy urgently.

242
00:11:03,720 --> 00:11:04,360
Mr. Cai,

243
00:11:04,720 --> 00:11:06,080
my company is having

244
00:11:06,080 --> 00:11:07,555
serious financial trouble right now.

245
00:11:07,577 --> 00:11:08,440
I really do need to

246
00:11:08,440 --> 00:11:09,680
sell this place.

247
00:11:11,400 --> 00:11:12,800
If you're buying it

248
00:11:12,800 --> 00:11:14,360
just to help me,

249
00:11:15,480 --> 00:11:16,720
I truly appreciate it.

250
00:11:17,240 --> 00:11:17,840
But you

251
00:11:19,040 --> 00:11:20,120
don't have to do this.

252
00:11:30,160 --> 00:11:32,120
Lin, you've got it wrong.

253
00:11:33,240 --> 00:11:34,560
I'm not helping you.

254
00:11:35,520 --> 00:11:36,680
I'm helping my daughter.

255
00:11:37,640 --> 00:11:39,000
Who said I don't need this place?

256
00:11:39,440 --> 00:11:40,720
I need it very much.

257
00:11:41,800 --> 00:11:42,760
It's for my daughter.

258
00:11:45,760 --> 00:11:46,640
You mean

259
00:11:46,720 --> 00:11:48,040
we can stay here?

260
00:11:48,733 --> 00:11:49,800
What else did you think?

261
00:11:55,960 --> 00:11:57,680
Your company's in trouble.

262
00:11:58,760 --> 00:12:00,440
You have a lot to deal with.

263
00:12:01,733 --> 00:12:03,240
I've been through tough times, too.

264
00:12:03,822 --> 00:12:05,760
The harder it gets,
the fewer people you have.

265
00:12:06,377 --> 00:12:07,520
The fewer people you have,

266
00:12:07,520 --> 00:12:08,840
the more each person has to do.

267
00:12:09,155 --> 00:12:10,422
In a situation like that,

268
00:12:11,111 --> 00:12:12,911
where would you find the time to move?

269
00:12:13,920 --> 00:12:15,800
The best solution is to stay put.

270
00:12:16,920 --> 00:12:17,960
I'll buy the place

271
00:12:18,133 --> 00:12:19,840
and rent it back to you. Problem solved.

272
00:12:20,960 --> 00:12:22,960
Lin, when you had this place,

273
00:12:24,040 --> 00:12:25,360
Zhangzhu lived here for free.

274
00:12:25,360 --> 00:12:26,920
You never charged a single dime.

275
00:12:28,320 --> 00:12:29,640
Now Zhangzhu has a place.

276
00:12:29,960 --> 00:12:31,600
Lin, if you feel bad

277
00:12:31,600 --> 00:12:32,640
about it,

278
00:12:33,480 --> 00:12:34,480
you can pay rent.

279
00:12:39,560 --> 00:12:40,760
Ms. Lin, I think that works.

280
00:12:41,520 --> 00:12:42,440
What do you think?

281
00:12:48,080 --> 00:12:48,600
Then...

282
00:12:50,320 --> 00:12:51,520
I'll sell it at a lower price.

283
00:12:51,760 --> 00:12:52,160
No need.

284
00:12:52,600 --> 00:12:53,400
No need, really.

285
00:12:54,000 --> 00:12:55,320
Just pay a higher rent.

286
00:12:55,760 --> 00:12:56,760
It all balances out.

287
00:13:00,200 --> 00:13:00,560
Alright.

288
00:13:01,355 --> 00:13:02,840
I need to return to the dinner.

289
00:13:03,600 --> 00:13:04,760
Don't be so clueless.

290
00:13:05,080 --> 00:13:06,400
The more your boss needs you,

291
00:13:06,400 --> 00:13:08,888
the more you need to step up
and hold things together.

292
00:13:10,920 --> 00:13:11,760
You should go

293
00:13:11,760 --> 00:13:13,044
before they finish eating.

294
00:13:15,280 --> 00:13:15,920
Mr. Cai.

295
00:13:20,000 --> 00:13:20,560
Thank you.

296
00:13:23,480 --> 00:13:23,840
I'm off.

297
00:13:24,600 --> 00:13:25,520
Don't drink too much.

298
00:13:31,200 --> 00:13:32,066
Let me tell you.

299
00:13:32,288 --> 00:13:34,111
My dad may be unreliable
in everything else,

300
00:13:34,320 --> 00:13:36,120
but when it comes to property,

301
00:13:36,120 --> 00:13:37,120
he's extremely reliable.

302
00:13:37,360 --> 00:13:38,960
If there were a god of real estate,

303
00:13:39,022 --> 00:13:40,340
my dad would definitely know him.

304
00:13:42,480 --> 00:13:44,080
Don't feel awkward, Ms. Lin.

305
00:13:44,777 --> 00:13:46,400
The one who should feel awkward is me.

306
00:13:47,080 --> 00:13:48,040
Look at this.

307
00:13:48,133 --> 00:13:49,955
I just own a whole house
in five minutes.

308
00:13:50,760 --> 00:13:52,360
I should be thanking you, Zhangzhu.

309
00:13:54,000 --> 00:13:54,933
Don't mention it.

310
00:13:56,622 --> 00:13:57,120
Oh, right.

311
00:13:58,080 --> 00:13:58,960
You have a package.

312
00:13:59,120 --> 00:14:00,533
It's from Colorful Culture Media.

313
00:14:10,460 --> 00:14:12,900
(Zhao Lanxin and Ling Yikai
cordially invite you to the wedding.)

314
00:14:13,520 --> 00:14:14,880
Zhao Lanxin's getting married?

315
00:14:17,520 --> 00:14:18,920
She finally got her wish.

316
00:14:22,160 --> 00:14:23,560
Is your place all tidied up?

317
00:14:25,360 --> 00:14:25,880
No.

318
00:14:28,200 --> 00:14:29,400
It's too small.

319
00:14:29,466 --> 00:14:30,600
We can't both live there.

320
00:14:31,320 --> 00:14:31,880
Too small?

321
00:14:32,040 --> 00:14:33,400
You want to get a bigger place?

322
00:14:33,600 --> 00:14:34,600
What I mean is

323
00:14:35,240 --> 00:14:36,720
you shouldn't move in for now.

324
00:14:38,066 --> 00:14:39,080
Then you move in here.

325
00:14:39,244 --> 00:14:40,360
I'm not moving in either.

326
00:14:42,320 --> 00:14:43,720
I don't want to live with you.

327
00:14:45,440 --> 00:14:46,840
What do I tell people when they ask?

328
00:14:47,000 --> 00:14:48,000
Say whatever you want.

329
00:14:54,560 --> 00:14:55,920
I only agreed to marry you.

330
00:14:56,577 --> 00:14:58,688
I never said
we were going to live together.

331
00:14:59,440 --> 00:15:01,000
If you insist, fine,

332
00:15:01,622 --> 00:15:03,320
I'll be on business trips all the time.

333
00:15:07,000 --> 00:15:09,080
You're doing this on purpose
to make me look bad.

334
00:15:14,200 --> 00:15:15,920
I didn't force you to marry me.

335
00:15:16,911 --> 00:15:18,850
If you think it's not right,
don't get married.

336
00:15:19,266 --> 00:15:20,280
I really don't understand

337
00:15:20,280 --> 00:15:21,640
why you insist on marrying me.

338
00:15:21,640 --> 00:15:22,840
You know I don't want this.

339
00:15:23,622 --> 00:15:26,000
You're always afraid of looking awkward
in front of others.

340
00:15:26,080 --> 00:15:27,511
Aren't you afraid of facing yourself?

341
00:15:28,640 --> 00:15:30,200
Ling Yikai, I didn't tie you up

342
00:15:30,200 --> 00:15:31,444
and force you to marry me.

343
00:15:31,711 --> 00:15:34,244
You only said yes
after considering all the pros and cons.

344
00:15:34,355 --> 00:15:36,080
If anyone's afraid of facing themselves,

345
00:15:36,080 --> 00:15:37,680
it's you, not me.

346
00:15:48,311 --> 00:15:50,320
You're marrying someone
who doesn't love you.

347
00:15:50,688 --> 00:15:51,840
Do you think you'll be happy?

348
00:15:53,044 --> 00:15:54,844
I've never known what happiness is.

349
00:15:54,880 --> 00:15:56,622
So I don't know
what it's supposed to be.

350
00:15:57,000 --> 00:15:58,600
And I never planned to chase happiness.

351
00:15:59,533 --> 00:16:01,777
I only know I can't let people
look down on me anymore.

352
00:16:02,000 --> 00:16:03,280
What others have or don't have,

353
00:16:03,280 --> 00:16:04,600
I, Zhao Lanxin, will have it all.

354
00:16:05,360 --> 00:16:06,480
What I want is

355
00:16:06,720 --> 00:16:07,960
for people to see me

356
00:16:08,680 --> 00:16:10,440
and regret looking down on me

357
00:16:10,600 --> 00:16:12,200
and envy everything I have now.

358
00:16:13,480 --> 00:16:15,560
I want the kind of life
everyone sees as ideal.

359
00:16:16,000 --> 00:16:17,244
Aren't you the same?

360
00:16:19,880 --> 00:16:20,280
I am.

361
00:16:21,920 --> 00:16:22,400
I am.

362
00:16:23,600 --> 00:16:24,680
But your ideal life

363
00:16:24,760 --> 00:16:25,960
isn't necessarily mine.

364
00:16:32,800 --> 00:16:33,800
As for your ideal life...

365
00:16:34,866 --> 00:16:37,530
(New Perspective in Online Literature)
There's a forum on the 18th.

366
00:16:37,560 --> 00:16:39,280
It's about trends in online literature

367
00:16:39,560 --> 00:16:40,960
and investment outlook.

368
00:16:41,400 --> 00:16:42,440
They want to invite you

369
00:16:42,680 --> 00:16:43,720
to be the chair.

370
00:16:47,360 --> 00:16:48,866
So we live separately on weekdays

371
00:16:48,933 --> 00:16:50,422
and stay together on weekends.

372
00:17:00,000 --> 00:17:01,640
I'll definitely come over on weekends.

373
00:17:03,760 --> 00:17:05,600
One, I can take care of Grandma.

374
00:17:05,600 --> 00:17:08,760
Two, it makes your life look more ideal.

375
00:17:14,800 --> 00:17:16,880
Don't give me any trouble
before the wedding.

376
00:17:19,040 --> 00:17:20,720
No matter what I do,

377
00:17:21,466 --> 00:17:23,733
you'll still go through
with the wedding, right?

378
00:18:04,866 --> 00:18:06,266
You haven't eaten, right?

379
00:18:07,880 --> 00:18:09,080
I brought you something.

380
00:18:09,533 --> 00:18:10,360
I'll leave it here.

381
00:18:28,160 --> 00:18:31,280
You're going to write
15,000 words in one night?

382
00:18:34,600 --> 00:18:37,120
There are over 200 characters with names
in the novel.

383
00:18:38,560 --> 00:18:40,200
How are you going to wrap up

384
00:18:40,800 --> 00:18:42,320
in such a short length?

385
00:18:50,160 --> 00:18:51,520
Even if you finish it,

386
00:18:52,600 --> 00:18:54,200
Dingqi will reject it.

387
00:18:57,640 --> 00:18:58,800
If they don't publish it,

388
00:18:58,911 --> 00:18:59,840
I'll publish it myself.

389
00:20:07,378 --> 00:20:11,498
(WeChat: 1,367 unread messages)

390
00:20:16,180 --> 00:20:22,740
(The End)

391
00:20:25,555 --> 00:20:26,600
This is way too rushed.

392
00:20:26,680 --> 00:20:28,120
So many characters die.

393
00:20:28,911 --> 00:20:31,288
(Chapter 531: No More Gods (Finale))
What's wrong with He Han's novel?

394
00:20:31,488 --> 00:20:32,560
He published it himself?

395
00:20:33,822 --> 00:20:35,066
Is he out of his right mind?

396
00:20:35,088 --> 00:20:36,360
What's happening here?

397
00:20:36,360 --> 00:20:37,560
(No More Gods (Finale))
It's over?

398
00:20:37,560 --> 00:20:38,120
Yeah.

399
00:20:38,120 --> 00:20:39,720
The ending

400
00:20:40,080 --> 00:20:40,800
came way too fast.

401
00:20:41,360 --> 00:20:42,480
This sloppy?

402
00:20:42,666 --> 00:20:44,177
Doesn't feel like Mr. He's usual style.

403
00:20:44,200 --> 00:20:45,577
(Chapter 531: No More Gods (Finale))

404
00:20:46,360 --> 00:20:47,160
It's over?

405
00:20:48,977 --> 00:20:49,920
That's way too rush.

406
00:20:49,920 --> 00:20:51,000
Come on.

407
00:20:51,155 --> 00:20:51,720
What's wrong?

408
00:20:51,960 --> 00:20:52,520
Look at this.

409
00:20:52,760 --> 00:20:53,520
Look.

410
00:20:54,533 --> 00:20:55,120
It's over?

411
00:20:55,377 --> 00:20:56,320
I can't believe this.

412
00:20:56,320 --> 00:20:57,400
He Han's work flopped again.

413
00:20:57,700 --> 00:21:01,740
(Chapter 531: No More Gods (Finale))

414
00:21:01,760 --> 00:21:03,440
He threw together a random ending.

415
00:21:04,280 --> 00:21:05,080
He's guilty.

416
00:21:05,288 --> 00:21:07,111
He got scared of being called out
for plagiarism

417
00:21:07,155 --> 00:21:08,288
by Phantom Knight's fans.

418
00:21:14,520 --> 00:21:15,720
What's He Han thinking?

419
00:21:16,320 --> 00:21:18,080
All the characters die all of a sudden.

420
00:21:18,311 --> 00:21:19,888
What is he trying to do?

421
00:21:23,120 --> 00:21:24,560
The comment section and fan groups

422
00:21:24,560 --> 00:21:25,440
are exploding

423
00:21:25,440 --> 00:21:26,800
right now.

424
00:21:26,911 --> 00:21:28,120
Even that Phantom Knight fan

425
00:21:28,600 --> 00:21:30,840
who used to attack him

426
00:21:30,880 --> 00:21:31,840
is piling on.

427
00:21:33,422 --> 00:21:34,311
Have you seen it?

428
00:21:37,240 --> 00:21:37,680
No.

429
00:21:38,760 --> 00:21:39,880
Not worthy of my time.

430
00:21:41,822 --> 00:21:42,755
He deserves this.

431
00:21:42,866 --> 00:21:43,990
I would call him out, too.

432
00:21:44,320 --> 00:21:44,760
Wait.

433
00:21:45,040 --> 00:21:46,400
Dingqi isn't

434
00:21:46,400 --> 00:21:47,240
doing anything.

435
00:21:47,240 --> 00:21:49,520
They're letting Mr. He
drown in the backlash?

436
00:21:53,000 --> 00:21:54,000
For Dingqi,

437
00:21:55,240 --> 00:21:55,960
good reviews

438
00:21:56,560 --> 00:21:57,160
or bad ones,

439
00:21:57,880 --> 00:21:58,720
it's all traffic.

440
00:22:01,040 --> 00:22:01,840
What about Dai Shan?

441
00:22:02,511 --> 00:22:03,720
Is she not doing anything?

442
00:22:04,880 --> 00:22:05,600
In my opinion,

443
00:22:05,760 --> 00:22:06,822
what do you call this?

444
00:22:06,880 --> 00:22:08,200
This is a shameless behavior.

445
00:22:11,120 --> 00:22:13,680
Yeah. He didn't follow the rules before,
which is fine.

446
00:22:13,680 --> 00:22:15,200
I let it slide.

447
00:22:15,600 --> 00:22:16,240
But this time,

448
00:22:16,880 --> 00:22:17,440
sorry.

449
00:22:18,111 --> 00:22:21,920
I'm settling accounts
with him one by one, properly.

450
00:22:21,920 --> 00:22:23,733
(Publishing Rights
Acquisition Agreement)

451
00:22:24,680 --> 00:22:26,160
You settle your account with him,

452
00:22:26,920 --> 00:22:27,960
and I'll settle mine.

453
00:22:32,640 --> 00:22:33,800
You mean...

454
00:22:34,160 --> 00:22:36,440
If I'm not making money,
why would I stay?

455
00:23:01,400 --> 00:23:01,920
Coming.

456
00:23:11,040 --> 00:23:11,880
Just you?

457
00:23:12,000 --> 00:23:12,955
Where's Dai Shan?

458
00:23:13,720 --> 00:23:14,200
She left.

459
00:23:20,000 --> 00:23:20,960
To be precise,

460
00:23:21,480 --> 00:23:22,400
she resigned.

461
00:23:23,680 --> 00:23:25,360
When are you going to talk to him?

462
00:23:26,440 --> 00:23:27,160
I'm going now.

463
00:23:28,422 --> 00:23:29,480
I'll find another time.

464
00:23:30,720 --> 00:23:31,688
I'll go a bit later.

465
00:23:32,120 --> 00:23:34,240
She doesn't want to be
your editor anymore.

466
00:23:36,480 --> 00:23:38,360
She left calmly.

467
00:23:39,400 --> 00:23:40,520
Decisively.

468
00:23:42,440 --> 00:23:44,560
That means there was nothing

469
00:23:45,160 --> 00:23:46,160
worth staying for

470
00:23:46,160 --> 00:23:47,720
in working with you.

471
00:23:48,160 --> 00:23:49,480
You never made her feel

472
00:23:50,320 --> 00:23:51,480
anything for you.

473
00:23:52,440 --> 00:23:54,120
It was nothing but purely a professional

474
00:23:54,680 --> 00:23:56,960
concern and care.

475
00:23:58,911 --> 00:23:59,920
What do you think?

476
00:24:00,680 --> 00:24:01,280
Me?

477
00:24:03,520 --> 00:24:04,400
I think the same.

478
00:24:06,680 --> 00:24:08,080
I came here

479
00:24:08,720 --> 00:24:10,520
to talk about some contract clauses.

480
00:24:10,640 --> 00:24:11,600
No, Mr. Fan.

481
00:24:11,866 --> 00:24:13,240
I don't understand that stuff.

482
00:24:13,250 --> 00:24:14,200
If you have any requests,

483
00:24:14,200 --> 00:24:15,680
summarize them and send them to me.

484
00:24:25,480 --> 00:24:25,840
Right.

485
00:24:27,880 --> 00:24:28,200
Yes.

486
00:24:28,280 --> 00:24:29,511
The car is mine. What's wrong?

487
00:24:32,960 --> 00:24:34,240
Car valuation?

488
00:24:36,222 --> 00:24:37,320
I didn't call anyone.

489
00:24:38,920 --> 00:24:39,480
Dai Shan?

490
00:24:41,640 --> 00:24:42,120
Alright.

491
00:24:42,920 --> 00:24:44,040
Okay.

492
00:24:45,860 --> 00:24:49,380
(Publishing Rights Acquisition Agreement
on Shattered Six States by He Han)

493
00:24:56,200 --> 00:24:58,360
If you like the car, you can have it.

494
00:24:58,640 --> 00:25:00,520
Why let a second-hand dealer take a cut?

495
00:25:02,360 --> 00:25:04,040
Transparent valuation

496
00:25:04,200 --> 00:25:05,822
makes settling accounts easier.

497
00:25:05,888 --> 00:25:07,280
You're the one handling the books.

498
00:25:07,280 --> 00:25:08,840
Whatever you say, I'll accept.

499
00:25:09,400 --> 00:25:11,640
Leave clean, and arrive clean.

500
00:25:11,640 --> 00:25:12,800
That's how business continues.

501
00:25:13,440 --> 00:25:14,800
So we'll still have dealings?

502
00:25:14,920 --> 00:25:15,840
Hard to say.

503
00:25:16,133 --> 00:25:17,955
Depends on how you develop
in the future.

504
00:25:18,022 --> 00:25:19,600
If you do well,

505
00:25:19,600 --> 00:25:21,680
I might come back.

506
00:25:22,080 --> 00:25:23,120
Cooperation is simple.

507
00:25:23,120 --> 00:25:24,640
If it fits, we work together.

508
00:25:25,440 --> 00:25:27,200
Friendship built on business

509
00:25:27,200 --> 00:25:30,240
lasts longer
than business built on friendship.

510
00:25:33,240 --> 00:25:35,000
Have you found your next friend yet?

511
00:25:35,920 --> 00:25:37,280
Or going back to Dingqi

512
00:25:37,360 --> 00:25:38,240
to split the pie?

513
00:25:38,360 --> 00:25:39,800
I'm not interested

514
00:25:39,800 --> 00:25:41,000
in his little company.

515
00:25:41,440 --> 00:25:43,200
Otherwise, I wouldn't have
come back to you.

516
00:25:43,200 --> 00:25:43,640
Right?

517
00:25:46,520 --> 00:25:46,960
Excuse me.

518
00:25:47,080 --> 00:25:48,550
We've photographed all the car details.

519
00:25:48,560 --> 00:25:50,080
We'll contact you
after the professional evaluation.

520
00:25:50,160 --> 00:25:50,920
Alright, thank you.

521
00:25:51,200 --> 00:25:51,790
You're welcome.

522
00:25:52,400 --> 00:25:55,680
The hotel manager will come
this afternoon to settle your bill.

523
00:25:55,680 --> 00:25:58,040
Normally, checkout is at 12 PM tomorrow,

524
00:25:58,155 --> 00:25:59,933
but your membership extends it to 4 PM.

525
00:26:02,200 --> 00:26:03,160
Thanks, really.

526
00:26:03,577 --> 00:26:05,680
You even remembered to check out
before you leave.

527
00:26:06,360 --> 00:26:07,680
There's a deposit with the hotel.

528
00:26:07,680 --> 00:26:08,640
I just want to make sure

529
00:26:08,640 --> 00:26:11,360
you'll have money left with me
after settling everything.

530
00:26:11,360 --> 00:26:12,480
It's not that serious.

531
00:26:12,480 --> 00:26:14,440
A starving camel
is still bigger than a horse.

532
00:26:16,320 --> 00:26:17,440
A friendly reminder.

533
00:26:17,960 --> 00:26:19,840
If you have money left,

534
00:26:19,840 --> 00:26:21,280
buy yourself

535
00:26:21,280 --> 00:26:23,560
a pension or medical insurance.

536
00:26:24,720 --> 00:26:26,040
In the future,

537
00:26:26,120 --> 00:26:28,080
you might not be
as wealthy as you think.

538
00:26:29,880 --> 00:26:30,640
Thanks a bunch.

539
00:26:31,000 --> 00:26:31,920
I'm still young.

540
00:27:31,680 --> 00:27:33,800
We can skip the contract.

541
00:27:33,880 --> 00:27:35,288
Let's keep things fair and proper.

542
00:27:35,288 --> 00:27:36,200
Keep it for now.

543
00:27:37,600 --> 00:27:38,920
It's funny when I think about it.

544
00:27:39,400 --> 00:27:40,760
Back then, I had nowhere to live,

545
00:27:40,960 --> 00:27:42,120
so I stayed at your place.

546
00:27:42,200 --> 00:27:42,640
And now

547
00:27:42,840 --> 00:27:43,720
it's become my house.

548
00:27:43,720 --> 00:27:45,400
And I'm the one collecting rent
from you.

549
00:27:45,560 --> 00:27:47,720
Your dad helped me a lot.

550
00:27:47,760 --> 00:27:49,640
Don't feel awkward about it.

551
00:27:50,555 --> 00:27:52,000
There's another copy on the table.

552
00:27:52,080 --> 00:27:53,080
Tell Zhou Mei to sign it.

553
00:27:53,360 --> 00:27:53,880
Ms. Lin,

554
00:27:55,280 --> 00:27:56,960
there's something I should

555
00:27:56,960 --> 00:27:58,120
report to you.

556
00:27:58,680 --> 00:28:00,600
Otherwise, you'll say
I'm hiding things again.

557
00:28:03,288 --> 00:28:04,400
What did He Han do now?

558
00:28:06,760 --> 00:28:08,040
He's moving out of the hotel.

559
00:28:09,280 --> 00:28:10,080
How do you know?

560
00:28:10,977 --> 00:28:12,560
Someone in the fan group noticed

561
00:28:12,560 --> 00:28:15,360
his room is available tomorrow.

562
00:28:15,800 --> 00:28:17,840
But that hotel only has one room

563
00:28:17,840 --> 00:28:19,000
with that layout, right?

564
00:28:26,640 --> 00:28:28,040
He has switched hotels before.

565
00:28:29,880 --> 00:28:32,240
I heard Dingqi asked him
to return the money.

566
00:28:33,000 --> 00:28:34,200
Dai Shan has left, too.

567
00:28:41,240 --> 00:28:42,440
What are you trying to say?

568
00:28:43,440 --> 00:28:45,200
I don't know if it's true.

569
00:28:46,800 --> 00:28:48,040
But if it is,

570
00:28:48,440 --> 00:28:50,760
I feel bad for Mr. He Han.

571
00:28:51,680 --> 00:28:52,240
Ms. Lin,

572
00:28:53,280 --> 00:28:55,000
if he's in trouble,

573
00:28:55,320 --> 00:28:56,400
will we help him?

574
00:29:00,440 --> 00:29:02,120
We're in big trouble ourselves.

575
00:29:05,000 --> 00:29:06,360
He still has some money.

576
00:29:06,555 --> 00:29:08,400
He won't be sleeping rough
on the street.

577
00:29:09,080 --> 00:29:09,600
Besides,

578
00:29:09,680 --> 00:29:10,640
he's an adult.

579
00:29:11,320 --> 00:29:12,120
He's able

580
00:29:12,120 --> 00:29:13,440
to take care of his own life.

581
00:29:16,288 --> 00:29:18,400
There's a contract
on the table. Sign it.

582
00:29:20,600 --> 00:29:22,720
Mei, maybe you shouldn't sign it.

583
00:29:23,480 --> 00:29:24,280
You didn't pay rent

584
00:29:24,680 --> 00:29:27,280
to Ms. Lin before either.

585
00:29:27,377 --> 00:29:29,088
Now that the place has changed hands,

586
00:29:29,133 --> 00:29:30,488
you'd end up paying rent.

587
00:29:30,600 --> 00:29:31,240
That won't do.

588
00:29:31,280 --> 00:29:32,800
I'll only feel at ease if I sign it.

589
00:29:33,200 --> 00:29:34,000
Before this,

590
00:29:34,080 --> 00:29:36,280
I always felt indebted.

591
00:29:36,311 --> 00:29:38,577
Even when someone criticized me,
I didn't dare talk back.

592
00:29:38,688 --> 00:29:40,120
I was trying to persuade you

593
00:29:40,480 --> 00:29:42,280
to turn back while you still could.

594
00:29:44,177 --> 00:29:45,600
From now on, if anything in the house

595
00:29:45,720 --> 00:29:47,000
needs fixing or replacing,

596
00:29:47,000 --> 00:29:48,040
feel free to tell me.

597
00:29:48,280 --> 00:29:49,360
My dad advised me

598
00:29:49,640 --> 00:29:50,760
that I should prepare you

599
00:29:50,760 --> 00:29:52,822
with good food, good drinks,
and nutritious meals.

600
00:29:52,844 --> 00:29:55,200
For breakfast,
I'll prepare milk and bread.

601
00:29:55,440 --> 00:29:55,880
Anyway,

602
00:29:56,320 --> 00:29:57,440
I'll take good care of you.

603
00:29:58,000 --> 00:29:58,400
Alright.

604
00:29:59,000 --> 00:29:59,480
It's signed.

605
00:29:59,760 --> 00:30:00,240
Okay.

606
00:30:00,933 --> 00:30:02,360
I'm heading out to meet a client.

607
00:30:05,080 --> 00:30:06,120
I'm going to see Gu Yan.

608
00:30:06,130 --> 00:30:07,550
There's a meeting later
this afternoon, too.

609
00:30:07,560 --> 00:30:08,440
I'll go with you.

610
00:30:08,840 --> 00:30:09,320
No need.

611
00:30:09,955 --> 00:30:11,022
It's an old project.

612
00:30:11,155 --> 00:30:12,266
You're not familiar with it.

613
00:30:18,120 --> 00:30:19,400
You're going to see a client?

614
00:30:20,911 --> 00:30:22,644
You're not worried about He Han?

615
00:30:38,160 --> 00:30:38,960
Mr. He,

616
00:30:39,280 --> 00:30:40,320
are you moving out?

617
00:30:41,320 --> 00:30:42,880
Hotels are for short stays.

618
00:30:43,600 --> 00:30:44,920
Madam, I don't need these anymore.

619
00:30:45,120 --> 00:30:46,520
If you like them, you can have them.

620
00:30:47,360 --> 00:30:49,280
This printer looks pretty new.

621
00:30:49,960 --> 00:30:51,360
These decorations are nice, too.

622
00:30:51,440 --> 00:30:52,720
If you like them, take them.

623
00:30:53,666 --> 00:30:54,760
Then I'll take them all.

624
00:30:54,844 --> 00:30:56,800
I still need those books.
Don't take the books.

625
00:30:56,840 --> 00:30:57,755
I don't want the books.

626
00:30:57,760 --> 00:30:58,760
Thank you, Mr. He.

627
00:31:06,560 --> 00:31:07,200
Let's celebrate.

628
00:31:09,240 --> 00:31:11,520
You've ended a short journey

629
00:31:11,960 --> 00:31:13,444
and are going to start a new chapter.

630
00:31:15,960 --> 00:31:17,360
You're really not doing

631
00:31:18,480 --> 00:31:19,360
He Han's new project?

632
00:31:20,640 --> 00:31:22,040
With the terms I offered,

633
00:31:22,600 --> 00:31:23,800
I might consider it.

634
00:31:24,000 --> 00:31:25,360
Your terms?

635
00:31:25,520 --> 00:31:27,120
He has to give up his rights and name.

636
00:31:29,920 --> 00:31:32,880
Even a third-rate author
might not accept them,

637
00:31:33,480 --> 00:31:34,440
let alone

638
00:31:34,800 --> 00:31:35,960
He Han.

639
00:31:39,080 --> 00:31:40,440
In the past,

640
00:31:40,440 --> 00:31:42,000
he could sell for a high price

641
00:31:42,520 --> 00:31:43,560
with just a title.

642
00:31:43,600 --> 00:31:44,688
I would've paid for it, too.

643
00:31:44,880 --> 00:31:45,720
But now,

644
00:31:47,360 --> 00:31:48,840
you can see

645
00:31:48,840 --> 00:31:49,955
an author's rise and fall,

646
00:31:49,960 --> 00:31:51,000
and so can I.

647
00:31:54,120 --> 00:31:54,760
Fan,

648
00:31:55,000 --> 00:31:57,880
isn't there a softer way?

649
00:31:59,520 --> 00:32:00,920
You've already resigned,

650
00:32:01,111 --> 00:32:02,733
and you're still thinking about him?

651
00:32:04,440 --> 00:32:05,760
We used to work together.

652
00:32:06,440 --> 00:32:07,840
I don't want him to suffer.

653
00:32:07,960 --> 00:32:08,880
We're a married couple.

654
00:32:09,040 --> 00:32:10,480
So you'd rather I suffer?

655
00:32:12,640 --> 00:32:13,240
You?

656
00:32:13,880 --> 00:32:15,560
You'll never be at a loss.

657
00:32:18,240 --> 00:32:19,480
We both see that.

658
00:32:19,920 --> 00:32:21,040
We know

659
00:32:21,480 --> 00:32:22,960
he's not in any state

660
00:32:22,960 --> 00:32:24,640
to write anything good right now.

661
00:32:25,240 --> 00:32:26,920
Whoever takes it seriously loses.

662
00:32:31,520 --> 00:32:32,360
I've arranged it.

663
00:32:33,111 --> 00:32:34,288
Come to my company.

664
00:32:35,440 --> 00:32:36,160
Come to Dingqi.

665
00:32:36,444 --> 00:32:37,520
You'll manage the editors

666
00:32:38,760 --> 00:32:40,080
and oversee

667
00:32:40,320 --> 00:32:41,800
all content planning.

668
00:32:45,840 --> 00:32:47,240
I never said I would join Dingqi.

669
00:32:47,355 --> 00:32:48,644
Where will you go then?

670
00:32:49,444 --> 00:32:50,760
No one can offer better terms

671
00:32:50,760 --> 00:32:52,360
than I can.

672
00:32:52,760 --> 00:32:54,200
You expect me to believe that?

673
00:32:54,520 --> 00:32:56,400
I should at least ask around

674
00:32:56,880 --> 00:32:57,440
and compare.

675
00:32:57,560 --> 00:32:58,320
Who knows,

676
00:32:59,040 --> 00:33:00,560
there might be better offers out there.

677
00:33:01,280 --> 00:33:02,400
Impossible.

678
00:33:04,360 --> 00:33:06,080
Even if there are better offers,

679
00:33:06,080 --> 00:33:08,000
don't rush into anything.

680
00:33:08,360 --> 00:33:11,520
We can't judge everything by money.

681
00:33:13,200 --> 00:33:15,560
We're basically an industry giant now.

682
00:33:16,560 --> 00:33:17,600
It's no exaggeration to say

683
00:33:18,000 --> 00:33:19,000
we dominate the market.

684
00:33:19,920 --> 00:33:21,480
No matter who you work with,

685
00:33:21,600 --> 00:33:22,600
your bargaining power

686
00:33:22,600 --> 00:33:23,640
will still depend on us.

687
00:33:26,280 --> 00:33:27,120
That may be true now,

688
00:33:28,311 --> 00:33:29,680
but not necessarily in the future.

689
00:33:31,720 --> 00:33:33,680
Not within five years.

690
00:33:33,755 --> 00:33:36,400
We're like an aircraft carrier
in the industry.

691
00:33:37,400 --> 00:33:39,280
Smaller boats turn faster

692
00:33:40,560 --> 00:33:41,720
in vast waters.

693
00:34:05,480 --> 00:34:06,720
You said no more contact.

694
00:34:07,577 --> 00:34:08,755
Why are you looking for me?

695
00:34:13,400 --> 00:34:15,120
This is a complete mess.

696
00:34:18,320 --> 00:34:20,040
I don't have anyone to talk about it.

697
00:34:26,155 --> 00:34:28,511
Has work basically stopped for you
these past few days?

698
00:34:30,880 --> 00:34:31,640
Pretty much.

699
00:34:33,600 --> 00:34:34,680
I'm dealing with questioning

700
00:34:34,680 --> 00:34:36,560
and investigation from the authorities
every day.

701
00:34:37,840 --> 00:34:38,760
The worst part

702
00:34:41,040 --> 00:34:43,000
is facing my clients' doubts.

703
00:34:43,222 --> 00:34:44,280
I have to explain things

704
00:34:44,280 --> 00:34:45,920
to key clients one by one.

705
00:34:48,680 --> 00:34:50,240
How long do you think

706
00:34:51,440 --> 00:34:52,320
this will continue?

707
00:34:55,040 --> 00:34:55,600
No idea.

708
00:34:58,288 --> 00:34:59,680
Have you talked to Zhang Yousen?

709
00:35:03,640 --> 00:35:04,880
Have you met him recently?

710
00:35:07,000 --> 00:35:07,720
What did he say?

711
00:35:09,240 --> 00:35:10,222
Where are you going?

712
00:35:10,666 --> 00:35:12,220
Lawyer Bei sent me on a business trip.

713
00:35:12,444 --> 00:35:14,200
He's probably figuring out
how to deal with me

714
00:35:14,280 --> 00:35:15,550
without leaving any loose ends.

715
00:35:15,560 --> 00:35:17,444
You went straight for a ruthless move
against him

716
00:35:17,680 --> 00:35:18,760
like a reckless rookie.

717
00:35:20,088 --> 00:35:21,760
Didn't you think about how it would end

718
00:35:22,280 --> 00:35:23,640
when you reported him?

719
00:35:23,760 --> 00:35:25,880
No. Did you think about how it would end

720
00:35:25,880 --> 00:35:27,222
when you were with Lawyer Bei?

721
00:35:28,040 --> 00:35:28,720
None of us did.

722
00:35:29,111 --> 00:35:31,320
But if you ask me
whether I regret it, I don't.

723
00:35:31,800 --> 00:35:33,080
Right now, Lawyer Bei and I

724
00:35:33,080 --> 00:35:34,488
are standing on the edge of a cliff.

725
00:35:34,511 --> 00:35:36,355
If we jump, there's only one parachute.

726
00:35:36,600 --> 00:35:37,911
Whoever gets it survives.

727
00:35:39,680 --> 00:35:40,080
No.

728
00:35:42,444 --> 00:35:43,955
He said he was on a business trip.

729
00:35:48,520 --> 00:35:49,560
I sent him.

730
00:35:52,422 --> 00:35:54,311
What are you planning to do about him?

731
00:35:57,560 --> 00:35:59,480
He's probably prepared a way out.

732
00:36:01,320 --> 00:36:02,440
I sent him away on purpose.

733
00:36:03,080 --> 00:36:05,040
I want to see what cards
he has left to play.

734
00:36:15,480 --> 00:36:15,920
By the way,

735
00:36:18,200 --> 00:36:19,080
there's something

736
00:36:20,040 --> 00:36:21,240
I wish to tell you.

737
00:36:23,160 --> 00:36:25,160
I've asked my wife for a divorce.

738
00:36:29,480 --> 00:36:29,960
Excuse me.

739
00:36:30,133 --> 00:36:30,911
Here's your food.

740
00:36:48,555 --> 00:36:49,280
Enjoy your meal.

741
00:36:52,840 --> 00:36:53,200
Here.

742
00:36:54,040 --> 00:36:54,840
Eat something.

743
00:36:57,200 --> 00:36:57,800
I'm not eating.

744
00:36:59,080 --> 00:36:59,840
I have plans later.

745
00:37:01,530 --> 00:37:04,500
♪Keep chasing all♪

746
00:37:05,280 --> 00:37:06,760
Can you stay with me a little longer?

747
00:37:06,760 --> 00:37:10,050
♪And none of you ever know♪

748
00:37:12,430 --> 00:37:15,820
♪For a long time♪

749
00:37:17,900 --> 00:37:21,930
♪I hope to lean on your side♪

750
00:37:23,280 --> 00:37:24,480
Since we met,

751
00:37:26,711 --> 00:37:28,800
this is the first time
you've asked me to stay.

752
00:37:29,130 --> 00:37:32,470
♪Calling my name in the air♪

753
00:37:33,280 --> 00:37:34,960
It was hard back then

754
00:37:38,133 --> 00:37:40,244
just to ask you to stay a second longer.

755
00:37:40,266 --> 00:37:43,380
♪I see you at the end♪

756
00:37:45,550 --> 00:37:48,900
♪Now I cross the line♪

757
00:37:50,120 --> 00:37:55,410
♪To be with you, my love♪

758
00:38:14,240 --> 00:38:14,760
Gu Yan.

759
00:38:28,740 --> 00:38:30,980
(Parting with Yan Dan at Yishui,
Chapter 55: Crisis in the Shadows)

760
00:38:30,980 --> 00:38:32,460
(Chapter 215 Drunk Old Friend:
Hidden Depths)

761
00:38:35,022 --> 00:38:37,155
Why didn't you tell me
you were coming?

762
00:38:39,240 --> 00:38:40,280
I texted you.

763
00:38:40,755 --> 00:38:42,000
You probably didn't see it.

764
00:38:42,280 --> 00:38:43,080
I forgot my phone.

765
00:38:46,480 --> 00:38:47,520
Know your enemy

766
00:38:48,120 --> 00:38:48,880
and know yourself.

767
00:38:50,444 --> 00:38:52,155
What do you think of his writing?

768
00:38:52,880 --> 00:38:53,320
Not bad.

769
00:38:54,680 --> 00:38:56,280
He's competing with me for the top spot.

770
00:38:56,840 --> 00:38:59,800
But he's riding
on Phantom Knight's fame.

771
00:39:03,920 --> 00:39:05,200
What do you think about

772
00:39:05,880 --> 00:39:06,960
Sansan's background?

773
00:39:09,480 --> 00:39:10,000
A newcomer.

774
00:39:10,355 --> 00:39:12,160
Imitating Phantom Knight's
mysterious style.

775
00:39:13,520 --> 00:39:14,360
Background?

776
00:39:14,920 --> 00:39:15,320
No idea.

777
00:39:15,666 --> 00:39:16,560
People didn't know

778
00:39:16,560 --> 00:39:18,644
that I owned
an internet cafe either at first.

779
00:39:18,888 --> 00:39:20,800
Web novel authors
come from all walks of life.

780
00:39:21,266 --> 00:39:23,160
I don't think this person is a newcomer.

781
00:39:23,622 --> 00:39:24,600
He feels more like

782
00:39:24,880 --> 00:39:25,680
a seasoned one.

783
00:39:26,920 --> 00:39:27,440
How so?

784
00:39:28,160 --> 00:39:29,560
This is a big debut for a newbie.

785
00:39:30,200 --> 00:39:31,240
He would care more

786
00:39:31,800 --> 00:39:33,200
about naming.

787
00:39:36,560 --> 00:39:37,960
Sansan may sound casual

788
00:39:38,320 --> 00:39:39,680
to you,

789
00:39:40,040 --> 00:39:41,160
but to him,

790
00:39:41,440 --> 00:39:42,520
it probably means something.

791
00:39:44,320 --> 00:39:45,000
That makes sense.

792
00:39:46,040 --> 00:39:47,720
So after studying his work,

793
00:39:47,760 --> 00:39:48,960
did you figure something out?

794
00:39:53,560 --> 00:39:55,200
Or are you still upset

795
00:39:55,200 --> 00:39:56,560
I didn't let you write the sequel?

796
00:39:56,640 --> 00:39:57,755
You might've done better

797
00:39:57,880 --> 00:39:59,240
than Sansan.

798
00:40:04,520 --> 00:40:05,480
I'm not upset.

799
00:40:06,600 --> 00:40:07,080
You know

800
00:40:07,560 --> 00:40:08,640
I'm only grateful to you.

801
00:40:08,880 --> 00:40:09,755
I don't resent you.

802
00:40:10,600 --> 00:40:11,760
Even if I wrote it,

803
00:40:12,640 --> 00:40:14,120
I might not do better than Sansan.

804
00:40:14,866 --> 00:40:16,822
The blend of his style
and Phantom Knight's

805
00:40:17,000 --> 00:40:17,960
may not be seamless,

806
00:40:18,400 --> 00:40:20,280
but it's at least smooth and natural.

807
00:40:21,320 --> 00:40:22,800
I'll just focus on

808
00:40:23,040 --> 00:40:24,800
working on Drunk Old Friend.

809
00:40:26,600 --> 00:40:28,160
You've been submitting on time lately.

810
00:40:28,440 --> 00:40:29,360
The editors

811
00:40:29,360 --> 00:40:30,600
have no complaints.

812
00:40:30,755 --> 00:40:32,177
(Chapter 236: Trouble from Su)
They publish it right after.

813
00:40:32,480 --> 00:40:33,800
But let me remind you.

814
00:40:35,080 --> 00:40:36,320
If editors find no issues

815
00:40:37,000 --> 00:40:39,190
(Chapter 236: Trouble from Su)
and don't want to discuss it further,

816
00:40:39,200 --> 00:40:40,300
that itself is a problem.

817
00:40:40,622 --> 00:40:42,340
You won't lose readers
in the short term.

818
00:40:42,740 --> 00:40:43,620
But over time,

819
00:40:43,740 --> 00:40:45,300
all the problems will surface.

820
00:40:45,580 --> 00:40:46,620
By then,

821
00:40:46,955 --> 00:40:48,100
it'll be too late to fix it.

822
00:40:48,755 --> 00:40:50,244
I'll pay attention to that.

823
00:41:04,140 --> 00:41:04,660
Next week.

824
00:41:05,460 --> 00:41:06,540
The map changes soon.

825
00:41:07,380 --> 00:41:08,700
That's when you push harder.

826
00:41:09,140 --> 00:41:11,060
If the views and clicks

827
00:41:11,060 --> 00:41:12,100
don't go up,

828
00:41:12,780 --> 00:41:14,700
we'll have to deal with it together.

829
00:41:16,260 --> 00:41:17,060
You head back first.

830
00:41:17,580 --> 00:41:19,300
I'll plan next week's content.

831
00:41:19,444 --> 00:41:20,911
I'll call you if there's a problem.

832
00:41:22,260 --> 00:41:23,140
I'm free now.

833
00:41:23,266 --> 00:41:24,777
We can go through it together.

834
00:41:24,940 --> 00:41:25,380
No need.

835
00:41:54,822 --> 00:41:56,333
You guys are talking about work?

836
00:41:56,355 --> 00:41:57,380
I came at a bad time.

837
00:41:58,022 --> 00:41:59,444
You're here to see Gu Yan?

838
00:41:59,980 --> 00:42:02,340
Just maintaining relationships
with authors.

839
00:42:02,940 --> 00:42:04,420
He's from Chenxing,

840
00:42:04,511 --> 00:42:05,800
but you're not banning him

841
00:42:05,933 --> 00:42:07,311
from meeting others, right?

842
00:42:09,020 --> 00:42:09,740
Ms. Lin, Ms. Zhao.

843
00:42:10,300 --> 00:42:11,140
You should head back.

844
00:42:11,500 --> 00:42:12,340
I need to write.

845
00:42:12,777 --> 00:42:13,840
Sorry for the interruption.

846
00:42:14,044 --> 00:42:15,155
I'll come another time.

847
00:42:20,100 --> 00:42:21,900
She drops by sometimes.

848
00:42:22,340 --> 00:42:23,180
We talk about

849
00:42:23,300 --> 00:42:25,340
possible cooperation.

850
00:42:29,200 --> 00:42:31,488
You signed an eight-year contract
with Chenxing.

851
00:42:31,780 --> 00:42:32,660
It's airtight.

852
00:42:33,860 --> 00:42:35,020
Before it ends,

853
00:42:35,460 --> 00:42:36,700
you can't work with her.

854
00:42:37,933 --> 00:42:39,180
So what was there to talk about?

855
00:42:40,740 --> 00:42:41,900
Eight years from now?

856
00:42:44,060 --> 00:42:44,780
I don't know.

857
00:42:44,900 --> 00:42:46,540
Or maybe she's looking for loopholes.

858
00:42:47,540 --> 00:42:48,780
Lawyer Bei

859
00:42:49,260 --> 00:42:50,660
covered everything

860
00:42:50,755 --> 00:42:52,222
when drafting the contract.

861
00:42:53,022 --> 00:42:54,300
There can't be any loopholes.

862
00:42:54,644 --> 00:42:57,422
Right now, there are only two people
she needs to keep an eye on.

863
00:42:59,020 --> 00:42:59,540
Sansan

864
00:43:01,340 --> 00:43:01,940
and Ling Yikai.

865
00:43:05,921 --> 00:43:07,041
(I've been thinking.)

866
00:43:08,321 --> 00:43:11,601
(Everyone's most comfortable level of intimacy)

867
00:43:12,361 --> 00:43:19,691
(is probably different.)

868
00:43:20,691 --> 00:43:22,441
♪If the sky♪

869
00:43:22,951 --> 00:43:24,351
♪And the sea♪

870
00:43:24,891 --> 00:43:26,601
♪Turned upside down♪

871
00:43:28,161 --> 00:43:30,091
♪If a swimming fish♪

872
00:43:30,491 --> 00:43:33,881
♪Fell in love with a flying bird♪

873
00:43:35,651 --> 00:43:37,621
♪If back then♪

874
00:43:37,981 --> 00:43:42,391
♪We had never let go♪

875
00:43:42,991 --> 00:43:49,271
♪We wouldn't be lost in the crowd♪

876
00:43:50,391 --> 00:43:52,541
♪We met in a thirteenth month♪

877
00:43:52,541 --> 00:43:54,411
♪Held each other in a fifth season♪

878
00:43:54,591 --> 00:43:57,031
♪And found our way back whole♪

879
00:43:57,871 --> 00:44:00,041
♪So let this surging love♪

880
00:44:00,041 --> 00:44:04,471
♪Rise like tides that never fall♪

881
00:44:05,371 --> 00:44:07,551
♪If we're caught in a pouring rain♪

882
00:44:07,551 --> 00:44:08,641
♪That's alright♪

883
00:44:09,181 --> 00:44:09,931
♪If we're buried♪

884
00:44:09,931 --> 00:44:12,631
♪By passing years all the better♪

885
00:44:12,891 --> 00:44:15,071
♪At least we still can keep♪

886
00:44:15,251 --> 00:44:19,671
♪This one eternal photograph♪

887
00:44:35,431 --> 00:44:37,721
♪We're on misaligned tracks♪

888
00:44:37,721 --> 00:44:39,481
♪Running in opposite ways♪

889
00:44:39,601 --> 00:44:42,071
♪Searching all along the way♪

890
00:44:42,871 --> 00:44:45,031
♪For the fire of our younger hearts♪

891
00:44:45,221 --> 00:44:50,131
♪And the beauty lost in time♪

892
00:44:50,131 --> 00:44:53,651
♪This time don't lose each other again♪

893
00:44:53,891 --> 00:44:54,861
♪Only after loss♪

894
00:44:54,861 --> 00:44:57,491
♪Do we learn what truly matters most♪

895
00:44:57,901 --> 00:45:00,261
♪In another time and space♪

896
00:45:00,261 --> 00:45:01,821
♪We'll stay and walk together♪

897
00:45:01,821 --> 00:45:04,651
♪Till we grow old♪

898
00:45:05,611 --> 00:45:07,901
♪But still the sky will never♪

899
00:45:07,901 --> 00:45:10,571
♪Turn with the sea♪

900
00:45:13,091 --> 00:45:15,501
♪But still a swimming fish won't♪

901
